reviewText: Very good item , well described, Good seller

It was great concert, you can see Noel and Liam in best shape, month before they decided to finish Oasis. Great Sound and Great performance.

This review is more specific like me as fan:

"See The Best Rock, Britpop Band Concert Video Oasis - Live At Wembley Arena 2008

Recorded live at Wembley Arena, London, October 2008
Oasis were an English rock band formed in Manchester in 1991. Originally known as The Rain, the group was formed by Liam Gallagher (vocals and tambourine), Paul "Bonehead" Arthurs (guitar), Paul "Guigsy" McGuigan (bass guitar) and Tony McCarroll (drums, percussion), who were soon joined by Liam's older brother Noel Gallagher (lead guitar and vocals). They have had eight UK number-one singles and eight UK number-one albums, and won fifteen NME Awards, nine Q Awards, four MTV Europe Music Awards and six BRIT Awards, including one in 2007 for outstanding contribution to music and one for the best album of the last 30 years as voted by the BBC Radio 2 listeners; they have been nominated for three Grammy Awards"

I am proud to have and listen all volumen I can....
